Air Quality Data Pipeline
Overview

This program fetches and cleans daily air quality data (PM2.5, PM10, NO2, O3) for Maine, New Hampshire, and Vermont using the OpenAQ API.

Setup
Install Python 3.13 or newer.
Create and activate a virtual environment.

Install requirements:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Enter your API Key within the .env file.

Usage
Run from the command line:
python main.py --start 2025-09-01T00:00:00Z --end 2025-09-07T23:59:59Z --limit 200

Files and Folders
data/raw/ - raw JSONL files from API
data/clean/ - cleaned CSV output
data/fetch.log - log file for each run
.env - holds your API key (excluded from git)
main.py - main script

What It Does
Fetches data from OpenAQ by sensor and day.
Saves raw data to data/raw/.
Cleans and filters PM2.5 and O3 data.
Saves results to data/clean/ as a CSV.
Logs all activity and errors.

Notes
Uses .env for API key (not stored in code).
Handles retries and rate limits.
Known issue: some 500 errors from OpenAQ servers.